# The Video Truth Record (.vtr) - Dual-Licensing Strategy

This repository utilizes a **Dual-Licensing Strategy** to differentiate between the written specification and the reference implementation code. This ensures the integrity of the standard while promoting an open, reciprocally-protected software ecosystem.

## 1. Specification & Whitepaper (The "Idea")
**License:** [Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-ND 4.0)](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/)

All documents located in `vtr-standard/specs/` and `vtr-standard/whitepaper/` are licensed under CC BY-ND 4.0.
*   **You may:** Share, copy, and redistribute the material in any medium.
*   **You may NOT:** Distribute modified versions (derivatives) of these documents.

This protects the **official definition** of the VTR standard from fragmentation.

## 2. Proof-of-Concept & Validator Code (The "Implementation")
**License:** [VTR Public License (VTR-PL)](vtr-standard/poc/LICENSE)

All source code located in `vtr-standard/poc/` is licensed under the **VTR Public License (VTR-PL)**.
*   Based on **GNU AGPLv3** with **Commons Clause** and **Poison Pill** extensions.
*   Designed to prevent "walled gardens" and purely commercial capture of the validation infrastructure.
*   Requires strict reciprocity: modifications must be open-sourced under the same terms.

## Summary
*   **Read the docs?** You can share them, but don't change the standard's text.
*   **Run the code?** You must stay open and interoperable.

*See specific `LICENSE` files in subdirectories for full legal texts.*
